President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of Montana due to straight-line winds that occurred on June 10, 2021. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. This includes funding for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Jon K. Huss has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.